From 422f6858d2e1d99fd95c55a3a7bcf29ca04e137a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 00:11:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Examples: Add macOS-specific notes to custom GIR library

Signed-off-by: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
---
diff --git a/examples/mylib-gtk-meson/README.md b/examples/mylib-gtk-meson/README.md
index 18fa2e23b818284071a2efcceaf04e07edf2b4ef..382620d46dca7850c4fb9acf91e245c8b7278b3d 100644
--- a/examples/mylib-gtk-meson/README.md
+++ b/examples/mylib-gtk-meson/README.md
@@ -10,6 +10,13 @@
 meson setup _build --prefix=/usr --wipe && meson compile -C _build && sudo meson install -C _build
 ```
 
+<details>
+    <summary>Expand macOS instructions</summary>
+
+On macOS, `--prefix` depends on your package manager and architecture. Homebrew on macOS uses `/opt/homebrew` for `arm64` and `/usr/local` for `amd64`, MacPorts uses `/opt/local`.
+
+</details>
+
 To update the `gettext` i18n resources, you can use:
 
 ```shell
@@ -28,6 +35,13 @@
 ```shell
 ./example.js
 ```
+
+<details>
+    <summary>Expand macOS instructions</summary>
+
+On macOS, you need to manually run `DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH="/opt/homebrew/lib" gjs -m example.js` instead of `./example.js`, with `/opt/homebrew` being the `--prefix` you used for `meson setup`. Else GJS can't find libraries, and SIP prevents `DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH` from propagating from the script.
+
+</details>
 
